# Create Eleventy App

This is a starter template for [Eleventy](https://www.11ty.dev/).
You can check out the [Eleventy documentation](https://www.11ty.dev/docs/) or join the [Eleventy community on Discord](https://discord.gg/GBkBy9u) to get help and ask questions.

## Getting Started

### Start the development server

```sh
npm run start
```

### Build the site for production

```sh
npm run build
```

### Clean the output directory

```sh
npm run clean
```

## Customizing

### Adding a new page

To add a new page, create a new file in the `{{input}}` directory. For example, to create a new page at the URL `/about`, create a file at `{{input}}/about.md`.

### Adding a new layout

To add a new layout, create a new file in the `{{input}}/{{includes}}` directory. For example, to create a new layout for posts, create a file at `{{input}}/{{includes}}/post.njk`.

### Modifying the site metadata

To modify the site metadata, edit the `{{input}}/{{data}}/site.json` file. For example, to change the site title, edit the `title` property. Feel free to add or remove any properties you don't need. To use a property in a template, use the `site` variable. For example, to use the site title in a template, use `\{{ site.title }}` (Nunjucks syntax).
